            <thetext>The &quot;deprecatedMethodWarning&quot; method uses qx.lang.Function.getName to print the
name of the deprecated method. In some cases a wrong name is printed, which can lead
confusion since it is hard to relate the warning to the correct method call.

      new qx.ui.form.Button().set({
        value: &quot;juhu&quot;
      });
      
This code will report the method &quot;undefined:construct&quot; as deprecated but is should be
&quot;qx.ui.form.Button.setValue&quot;.</thetext>
